cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on generating synthetic images for training machine learning models for real-world tasks, specifically semantic segmentation and reactive obstacle avoidance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper leverages recent progress in image-to-image translation, which is a popular topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. Finally, the paper also involves training a quadcopter to fly through a cluttered environment, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
